    titleAr: 'تنافس الأشقاء: تحويل الصراع إلى تواصل',
    excerptEn: 'Sibling fights are inevitable, but they do not have to define your family. Learn how to transform rivalry into a foundation for lifelong bonds.',
    excerptAr: 'شجارات الأشقاء حتمية، لكن لا يجب أن تحدد عائلتك. تعلم كيفية تحويل التنافس إلى أساس لروابط مدى الحياة.',
    contentEn: [
      'If your children fight constantly, take a deep breath: sibling conflict is one of the most normal aspects of family life. In fact, it serves an important developmental purpose when managed well.',
      'Sibling relationships are often the first place children learn to negotiate, compromise, and resolve conflict. These are skills they will use throughout their lives in friendships, partnerships, and professional relationships.',
      'The most common mistake parents make is trying to determine who started the conflict and assigning blame. This actually reinforces competitive dynamics. Instead, focus on teaching both children problem-solving skills.',
      'Avoid comparing siblings, even positively. Saying "Why can\'t you be more like your sister?" is obviously harmful, but even "Your brother is so good at math" creates a competitive framework that fuels rivalry.',
      'Make sure each child gets dedicated one-on-one time with each parent. Much sibling rivalry stems from competition for parental attention and affection. When children feel securely connected, they compete less.',
      'Teach children to express their needs directly instead of through conflict. "I feel frustrated when you take my things without asking" is a skill that transforms not just sibling relationships but all relationships.',
      'If sibling rivalry has escalated to bullying, physical aggression, or is causing visible emotional distress, it is important to seek professional support. These patterns can have long-lasting effects if not addressed.',
    ],
