      'Perfectionism is one of the biggest stress amplifiers for high achievers. The gap between your impossibly high standards and reality creates a constant state of inadequacy that no achievement can fill.',
      'Learn to distinguish between productive stress, which motivates and energizes, and toxic stress, which depletes and damages. The difference is not in the intensity but in the recovery. If you cannot switch off, the stress has become toxic.',
      'Build recovery into your schedule the same way you build in meetings and deadlines. Rest is not something you earn after completing everything. It is a prerequisite for sustainable high performance.',
      'Redefine success to include wellbeing. If your definition of success requires the sacrifice of your health, relationships, or peace of mind, it is time to update that definition. True success is sustainable.',
      'Working with a counselor is not a sign of weakness for a high achiever. It is a strategic investment in your most important asset: yourself. The most successful people in the world have coaches and therapists.',
